30class V8_NODISCARD GraphAssembler::BlockInlineReduction {
31 public:
32 explicit BlockInlineReduction(GraphAssembler* gasm) : gasm_(gasm) {
33 DCHECK(!gasm_->inline_reductions_blocked_);
34 gasm_->inline_reductions_blocked_ = true;
35 }
36 ~BlockInlineReduction() {
37 DCHECK(gasm_->inline_reductions_blocked_);
38 gasm_->inline_reductions_blocked_ = false;
39 }
40
41 private:
42 GraphAssembler* gasm_;
43};

45GraphAssembler::GraphAssembler(
46 MachineGraph* mcgraph, Zone* zone, BranchSemantics default_branch_semantics,
47 base::Optional<NodeChangedCallback> node_changed_callback,
48 bool mark_loop_exits)
49 : temp_zone_(zone),
50 mcgraph_(mcgraph),
51 default_branch_semantics_(default_branch_semantics),
52 effect_(nullptr),
53 control_(nullptr),
54 node_changed_callback_(node_changed_callback),
55 inline_reducers_(zone),
56 inline_reductions_blocked_(false),
57 loop_headers_(zone),
58 mark_loop_exits_(mark_loop_exits) {
59 DCHECK_NE(default_branch_semantics_, BranchSemantics::kUnspecified);
60}

188TNode<BoolT> GraphAssembler::UintPtrLessThan(TNode<UintPtrT> left,
189 TNode<UintPtrT> right) {
190 return kSystemPointerSize == 8
191 ? Uint64LessThan(TNode<Uint64T>::UncheckedCast(left),
192 TNode<Uint64T>::UncheckedCast(right))
193 : Uint32LessThan(TNode<Uint32T>::UncheckedCast(left),
194 TNode<Uint32T>::UncheckedCast(right));
195}

201 TNode<Uint64T>::UncheckedCast(right))

203 TNode<Uint32T>::UncheckedCast(right));

241Node* GraphAssembler::IntPtrEqual(Node* left, Node* right) {
242 return WordEqual(left, right);
243}
244
245Node* GraphAssembler::TaggedEqual(Node* left, Node* right) {
246 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
247 return Word32Equal(left, right);
248 } else {
249 return WordEqual(left, right);
250 }
251}
252
253Node* GraphAssembler::SmiSub(Node* left, Node* right) {
254 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
255 return BitcastWord32ToWord64(Int32Sub(left, right));
256 } else {
257 return IntSub(left, right);
258 }
259}
260
261Node* GraphAssembler::SmiLessThan(Node* left, Node* right) {
262 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
263 return Int32LessThan(left, right);
264 } else {
265 return IntLessThan(left, right);
266 }
267}

306TNode<Uint32T> JSGraphAssembler::LoadElementsKind(TNode<Map> map) {
307 TNode<Uint8T> bit_field2 = EnterMachineGraph<Uint8T>(
308 LoadField<Uint8T>(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2(), map),
309 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
310 return TNode<Uint32T>::UncheckedCast(
311 Word32Shr(TNode<Word32T>::UncheckedCast(bit_field2),
312 Uint32Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift)));
313}

336#ifdef V8_MAP_PACKING
337TNode<Map> GraphAssembler::UnpackMapWord(Node* map_word) {
338 map_word = BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(map_word);
339 // TODO(wenyuzhao): Clear header metadata.
340 Node* map = WordXor(map_word, IntPtrConstant(Internals::kMapWordXorMask));
341 return TNode<Map>::UncheckedCast(BitcastWordToTagged(map));
342}
343
344Node* GraphAssembler::PackMapWord(TNode<Map> map) {
345 Node* map_word = BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(map);
346 Node* packed = WordXor(map_word, IntPtrConstant(Internals::kMapWordXorMask));
347 return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(packed);
348}
349#endif
350
351TNode<Map> GraphAssembler::LoadMap(Node* object) {
352 Node* map_word = Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), object,
353 HeapObject::kMapOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
354#ifdef V8_MAP_PACKING
355 return UnpackMapWord(map_word);
356#else
357 return TNode<Map>::UncheckedCast(map_word);
358#endif
359}

527class ArrayBufferViewAccessBuilder {
528 public:
529 explicit ArrayBufferViewAccessBuilder(JSGraphAssembler* assembler,
530 InstanceType instance_type,
531 std::set<ElementsKind> candidates)
532 : assembler_(assembler),
533 instance_type_(instance_type),
534 candidates_(std::move(candidates)) {
535 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(assembler_);
536 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
537 DCHECK(instance_type_ == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE ||
538 instance_type_ == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE);
539 }
540
541 bool maybe_rab_gsab() const {
542 if (candidates_.empty()) return true;
543 return !base::all_of(candidates_, [](auto e) {
544 return !IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(e);
545 });
546 }
547
548 base::Optional<int> TryComputeStaticElementShift() {
549 DCHECK(instance_type_ != JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
550 if (instance_type_ == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) return 0;
551 if (candidates_.empty()) return base::nullopt;
552 int shift = ElementsKindToShiftSize(*candidates_.begin());
553 if (!base::all_of(candidates_, [shift](auto e) {
554 return ElementsKindToShiftSize(e) == shift;
555 })) {
556 return base::nullopt;
557 }
558 return shift;
559 }
560
561 base::Optional<int> TryComputeStaticElementSize() {
562 DCHECK(instance_type_ != JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
563 if (instance_type_ == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) return 1;
564 if (candidates_.empty()) return base::nullopt;
565 int size = ElementsKindToByteSize(*candidates_.begin());
566 if (!base::all_of(candidates_, [size](auto e) {
567 return ElementsKindToByteSize(e) == size;
568 })) {
569 return base::nullopt;
570 }
571 return size;
572 }
573
574 TNode<UintPtrT> BuildLength(TNode<JSArrayBufferView> view,
575 TNode<Context> context) {
576 auto& a = *assembler_;
577
578 // Case 1: Normal (backed by AB/SAB) or non-length tracking backed by GSAB
579 // (can't go oob once constructed)
580 auto GsabFixedOrNormal = [&]() {
581 return MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayLength(),
582 view, UseInfo::Word());
583 };
584
585 // If we statically know we cannot have rab/gsab backed, we can simply
586 // load from the view.
587 if (!maybe_rab_gsab()) {
588 return GsabFixedOrNormal();
589 }
590
591 // Otherwise, we need to generate the checks for the view's bitfield.
592 TNode<Word32T> bitfield = a.EnterMachineGraph<Word32T>(
593 a.LoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBitField(),
594 view),
595 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
596 TNode<Word32T> length_tracking_bit = a.Word32And(
597 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsLengthTracking));
598 TNode<Word32T> backed_by_rab_bit = a.Word32And(
599 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsBackedByRab));
600
601 // Load the underlying buffer.
602 TNode<HeapObject> buffer = a.LoadField<HeapObject>(
603 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(), view);
604
605 // Compute the element size.
606 TNode<Uint32T> element_size;
607 if (auto size_opt = TryComputeStaticElementSize()) {
608 element_size = a.Uint32Constant(*size_opt);
609 } else {
610 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type_, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE);
611 TNode<Map> typed_array_map = a.LoadField<Map>(
612 AccessBuilder::ForMap(WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier), view);
613 TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind = a.LoadElementsKind(typed_array_map);
614 element_size = a.LookupByteSizeForElementsKind(elements_kind);
615 }
616
617 // 2) Fixed length backed by RAB (can go oob once constructed)
618 auto RabFixed = [&]() {
619 TNode<UintPtrT> unchecked_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
620 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(), view,
621 UseInfo::Word());
622 TNode<UintPtrT> underlying_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
623 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
624 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
625 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
626 UseInfo::Word());
627
628 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length =
629 a
630 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(
631 a.UintPtrAdd(byte_offset, unchecked_byte_length),
632 underlying_byte_length))
633 .Then([&]() { return unchecked_byte_length; })
634 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
635 .Value();
636 return a.UintPtrDiv(byte_length, a.ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(element_size));
637 };
638
639 // 3) Length-tracking backed by RAB (JSArrayBuffer stores the length)
640 auto RabTracking = [&]() {
641 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
642 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
643 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
644 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
645 UseInfo::Word());
646
647 return a
648 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(
649 a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(byte_offset, byte_length))
650 .Then([&]() {
651 // length = floor((byte_length - byte_offset) / element_size)
652 return a.UintPtrDiv(a.UintPtrSub(byte_length, byte_offset),
653 a.ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(element_size));
654 })
655 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
656 .ExpectTrue()
657 .Value();
658 };
659
660 // 4) Length-tracking backed by GSAB (BackingStore stores the length)
661 auto GsabTracking = [&]() {
662 TNode<Number> temp = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(a.TypeGuard(
663 TypeCache::Get()->kJSArrayBufferViewByteLengthType,
664 a.JSCallRuntime1(Runtime::kGrowableSharedArrayBufferByteLength,
665 buffer, context, base::nullopt,
666 Operator::kNoWrite)));
667 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length =
668 a.EnterMachineGraph<UintPtrT>(temp, UseInfo::Word());
669 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
670 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
671 UseInfo::Word());
672
673 return a
674 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(
675 a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(byte_offset, byte_length))
676 .Then([&]() {
677 // length = floor((byte_length - byte_offset) / element_size)
678 return a.UintPtrDiv(a.UintPtrSub(byte_length, byte_offset),
679 a.ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(element_size));
680 })
681 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
682 .ExpectTrue()
683 .Value();
684 };
685
686 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(length_tracking_bit)
687 .Then([&]() {
688 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(backed_by_rab_bit)
689 .Then(RabTracking)
690 .Else(GsabTracking)
691 .Value();
692 })
693 .Else([&]() {
694 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(backed_by_rab_bit)
695 .Then(RabFixed)
696 .Else(GsabFixedOrNormal)
697 .Value();
698 })
699 .Value();
700 }
701
702 TNode<UintPtrT> BuildByteLength(TNode<JSArrayBufferView> view,
703 TNode<Context> context) {
704 auto& a = *assembler_;
705
706 // Case 1: Normal (backed by AB/SAB) or non-length tracking backed by GSAB
707 // (can't go oob once constructed)
708 auto GsabFixedOrNormal = [&]() {
709 return MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
710 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(), view,
711 UseInfo::Word());
712 };
713
714 // If we statically know we cannot have rab/gsab backed, we can simply
715 // use load from the view.
716 if (!maybe_rab_gsab()) {
717 return GsabFixedOrNormal();
718 }
719
720 // Otherwise, we need to generate the checks for the view's bitfield.
721 TNode<Word32T> bitfield = a.EnterMachineGraph<Word32T>(
722 a.LoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBitField(),
723 view),
724 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
725 TNode<Word32T> length_tracking_bit = a.Word32And(
726 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsLengthTracking));
727 TNode<Word32T> backed_by_rab_bit = a.Word32And(
728 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsBackedByRab));
729
730 // Load the underlying buffer.
731 TNode<HeapObject> buffer = a.LoadField<HeapObject>(
732 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(), view);
733
734 // Case 2: Fixed length backed by RAB (can go oob once constructed)
735 auto RabFixed = [&]() {
736 TNode<UintPtrT> unchecked_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
737 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(), view,
738 UseInfo::Word());
739 TNode<UintPtrT> underlying_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
740 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
741 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
742 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
743 UseInfo::Word());
744
745 return a
746 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(
747 a.UintPtrAdd(byte_offset, unchecked_byte_length),
748 underlying_byte_length))
749 .Then([&]() { return unchecked_byte_length; })
750 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
751 .Value();
752 };
753
754 auto RoundDownToElementSize = [&](TNode<UintPtrT> byte_size) {
755 if (auto shift_opt = TryComputeStaticElementShift()) {
756 constexpr uintptr_t all_bits = static_cast<uintptr_t>(-1);
757 if (*shift_opt == 0) return byte_size;
758 return TNode<UintPtrT>::UncheckedCast(
759 a.WordAnd(byte_size, a.UintPtrConstant(all_bits << (*shift_opt))));
760 }
761 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type_, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE);
762 TNode<Map> typed_array_map = a.LoadField<Map>(
763 AccessBuilder::ForMap(WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier), view);
764 TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind = a.LoadElementsKind(typed_array_map);
765 TNode<Uint32T> element_shift =
766 a.LookupByteShiftForElementsKind(elements_kind);
767 return TNode<UintPtrT>::UncheckedCast(
768 a.WordShl(a.WordShr(byte_size, element_shift), element_shift));
769 };
770
771 // Case 3: Length-tracking backed by RAB (JSArrayBuffer stores the length)
772 auto RabTracking = [&]() {
773 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
774 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
775 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
776 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
777 UseInfo::Word());
778
779 return a
780 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(
781 a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(byte_offset, byte_length))
782 .Then([&]() {
783 return RoundDownToElementSize(
784 a.UintPtrSub(byte_length, byte_offset));
785 })
786 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
787 .ExpectTrue()
788 .Value();
789 };
790
791 // Case 4: Length-tracking backed by GSAB (BackingStore stores the length)
792 auto GsabTracking = [&]() {
793 TNode<Number> temp = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(a.TypeGuard(
794 TypeCache::Get()->kJSArrayBufferViewByteLengthType,
795 a.JSCallRuntime1(Runtime::kGrowableSharedArrayBufferByteLength,
796 buffer, context, base::nullopt,
797 Operator::kNoWrite)));
798 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_length =
799 a.EnterMachineGraph<UintPtrT>(temp, UseInfo::Word());
800 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
801 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
802 UseInfo::Word());
803
804 return a
805 .MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(
806 a.UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(byte_offset, byte_length))
807 .Then([&]() {
808 return RoundDownToElementSize(
809 a.UintPtrSub(byte_length, byte_offset));
810 })
811 .Else([&]() { return a.UintPtrConstant(0); })
812 .ExpectTrue()
813 .Value();
814 };
815
816 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(length_tracking_bit)
817 .Then([&]() {
818 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(backed_by_rab_bit)
819 .Then(RabTracking)
820 .Else(GsabTracking)
821 .Value();
822 })
823 .Else([&]() {
824 return a.MachineSelectIf<UintPtrT>(backed_by_rab_bit)
825 .Then(RabFixed)
826 .Else(GsabFixedOrNormal)
827 .Value();
828 })
829 .Value();
830 }
831
832 TNode<Word32T> BuildDetachedCheck(TNode<JSArrayBufferView> view) {
833 auto& a = *assembler_;
834
835 // Load the underlying buffer and its bitfield.
836 TNode<HeapObject> buffer = a.LoadField<HeapObject>(
837 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(), view);
838 TNode<Word32T> buffer_bit_field =
839 MachineLoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField(),
840 buffer, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
841 // Mask the detached bit.
842 TNode<Word32T> detached_bit =
843 a.Word32And(buffer_bit_field,
844 a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask));
845
846 // If we statically know we cannot have rab/gsab backed, we are done here.
847 if (!maybe_rab_gsab()) {
848 return detached_bit;
849 }
850
851 // Otherwise, we need to generate the checks for the view's bitfield.
852 TNode<Word32T> bitfield = a.EnterMachineGraph<Word32T>(
853 a.LoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBitField(),
854 view),
855 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
856 TNode<Word32T> length_tracking_bit = a.Word32And(
857 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsLengthTracking));
858 TNode<Word32T> backed_by_rab_bit = a.Word32And(
859 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBufferView::kIsBackedByRab));
860
861 auto RabLengthTracking = [&]() {
862 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
863 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
864 UseInfo::Word());
865
866 TNode<UintPtrT> underlying_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
867 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
868
869 return a.Word32Or(detached_bit,
870 a.UintPtrLessThan(underlying_byte_length, byte_offset));
871 };
872
873 auto RabFixed = [&]() {
874 TNode<UintPtrT> unchecked_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
875 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(), view,
876 UseInfo::Word());
877 TNode<UintPtrT> byte_offset = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
878 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(), view,
879 UseInfo::Word());
880
881 TNode<UintPtrT> underlying_byte_length = MachineLoadField<UintPtrT>(
882 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferByteLength(), buffer, UseInfo::Word());
883
884 return a.Word32Or(
885 detached_bit,
886 a.UintPtrLessThan(underlying_byte_length,
887 a.UintPtrAdd(byte_offset, unchecked_byte_length)));
888 };
889
890 // Dispatch depending on rab/gsab and length tracking.
891 return a.MachineSelectIf<Word32T>(backed_by_rab_bit)
892 .Then([&]() {
893 return a.MachineSelectIf<Word32T>(length_tracking_bit)
894 .Then(RabLengthTracking)
895 .Else(RabFixed)
896 .Value();
897 })
898 .Else([&]() { return detached_bit; })
899 .Value();
900 }
901
902 private:
903 template <typename T>
904 TNode<T> MachineLoadField(FieldAccess const& access, TNode<HeapObject> object,
905 const UseInfo& use_info) {
906 return assembler_->EnterMachineGraph<T>(
907 assembler_->LoadField<T>(access, object), use_info);
908 }
909
910 JSGraphAssembler* assembler_;
911 InstanceType instance_type_;
912 std::set<ElementsKind> candidates_;
913};

936void JSGraphAssembler::CheckIfTypedArrayWasDetached(
937 TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array,
938 std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds_candidates,
939 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
940 ArrayBufferViewAccessBuilder builder(this, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
941 std::move(elements_kinds_candidates));
942
943 TNode<Word32T> detached_check = builder.BuildDetachedCheck(typed_array);
944 TNode<Boolean> is_not_detached =
945 ExitMachineGraph<Boolean>(Word32Equal(detached_check, Uint32Constant(0)),
946 MachineRepresentation::kBit, Type::Boolean());
947 CheckIf(is_not_detached, DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached, feedback);
948}

950TNode<Uint32T> JSGraphAssembler::LookupByteShiftForElementsKind(
951 TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind) {
952 TNode<UintPtrT> index = ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(Int32Sub(
953 elements_kind, Uint32Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)));
954 TNode<RawPtrT> shift_table = TNode<RawPtrT>::UncheckedCast(ExternalConstant(
955 ExternalReference::
956 typed_array_and_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements_kind_shifts()));
957 return TNode<Uint8T>::UncheckedCast(
958 Load(MachineType::Uint8(), shift_table, index));
959}
960
961TNode<Uint32T> JSGraphAssembler::LookupByteSizeForElementsKind(
962 TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind) {
963 TNode<UintPtrT> index = ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(Int32Sub(
964 elements_kind, Uint32Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)));
965 TNode<RawPtrT> size_table = TNode<RawPtrT>::UncheckedCast(ExternalConstant(
966 ExternalReference::
967 typed_array_and_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements_kind_sizes()));
968 return TNode<Uint8T>::UncheckedCast(
969 Load(MachineType::Uint8(), size_table, index));
970}

1039Node* GraphAssembler::AdaptLocalArgument(Node* argument) {
1040#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_LOCAL
1041 // With direct locals, the argument can be passed directly.
1042 return BitcastTaggedToWord(argument);
1043#else
1044 // With indirect locals, the argument has to be stored on the stack and the
1045 // slot address is passed.
1046 Node* stack_slot = StackSlot(sizeof(uintptr_t), alignof(uintptr_t), true);
1047 Store(StoreRepresentation(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
1048 kNoWriteBarrier),
1049 stack_slot, 0, BitcastTaggedToWord(argument));
1050 return stack_slot;
1051#endif
1052}

1188
1189void GraphAssembler::TailCall(const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
1190 int inputs_size, Node** inputs) {
1191#ifdef DEBUG
1192 static constexpr int kTargetEffectControl = 3;
1193 DCHECK_EQ(inputs_size,
1194 call_descriptor->ParameterCount() + kTargetEffectControl);
1195#endif // DEBUG
1196
1197 Node* node = AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->TailCall(call_descriptor),
1198 inputs_size, inputs));
1199
1200 // Unlike ConnectUnreachableToEnd, the TailCall node terminates a block; to
1201 // keep it live, it *must* be connected to End (also in Turboprop schedules).
1202 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), node);
1203
1204 // Setting effect, control to nullptr effectively terminates the current block
1205 // by disallowing the addition of new nodes until a new label has been bound.
1206 InitializeEffectControl(nullptr, nullptr);
1207}
1208
1209void GraphAssembler::BranchWithCriticalSafetyCheck(
1210 Node* condition, GraphAssemblerLabel<0u>* if_true,
1211 GraphAssemblerLabel<0u>* if_false) {
1212 BranchHint hint = BranchHint::kNone;
1213 if (if_true->IsDeferred() != if_false->IsDeferred()) {
1214 hint = if_false->IsDeferred() ? BranchHint::kTrue : BranchHint::kFalse;
1215 }
1216
1217 BranchImpl(default_branch_semantics_, condition, if_true, if_false, hint);
1218}
1219
1220void GraphAssembler::ConnectUnreachableToEnd() {
1221 DCHECK_EQ(effect()->opcode(), IrOpcode::kUnreachable);
1222 Node* throw_node = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), effect(), control());
1223 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
1224 if (node_changed_callback_.has_value()) {
1225 (*node_changed_callback_)(graph()->end());
1226 }
1227 effect_ = control_ = mcgraph()->Dead();
1228}

1230Node* GraphAssembler::AddClonedNode(Node* node) {
1231 DCHECK(node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
1232 UpdateEffectControlWith(node);
1233 return node;
1234}

1236Node* GraphAssembler::AddNode(Node* node) {
1237 if (!inline_reducers_.empty() && !inline_reductions_blocked_) {
1238 // Reducers may add new nodes to the graph using this graph assembler,
1239 // however they should never introduce nodes that need further reduction,
1240 // so block reduction
1241 BlockInlineReduction scope(this);
1242 Reduction reduction;
1243 for (auto reducer : inline_reducers_) {
1244 reduction = reducer->Reduce(node, nullptr);
1245 if (reduction.Changed()) break;
1246 }
1247 if (reduction.Changed()) {
1248 Node* replacement = reduction.replacement();
1249 if (replacement != node) {
1250 // Replace all uses of node and kill the node to make sure we don't
1251 // leave dangling dead uses.
1252 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(node, replacement, effect(), control());
1253 node->Kill();
1254 return replacement;
1255 }
1256 }
1257 }
1258
1259 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kTerminate) {
1260 return node;
1261 }
1262
1263 UpdateEffectControlWith(node);
1264 return node;
1265}

1273 effect_ = effect;

1277Operator const* JSGraphAssembler::PlainPrimitiveToNumberOperator() {
1278 if (!to_number_operator_.is_set()) {
1279 Callable callable =
1280 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber);
1281 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNoFlags;
1282 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1283 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
1284 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), flags,
1285 Operator::kEliminatable);
1286 to_number_operator_.set(common()->Call(call_descriptor));
1287 }
1288 return to_number_operator_.get();
1289}
